cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SY, cs.CE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with the AS-level topology of the Internet. Other likely sub-categories include cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as the paper discusses the structure of the Internet and its nodes, cs.SD (Software Engineering) as the paper may involve software tools for analyzing the Internet topology, cs.SY (Systems and Control) as the paper may involve control systems for managing the Internet, and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) as the paper may involve computational methods for analyzing the Internet topology.
